records.addlTxt:
Defendant Travis A Rehberg in court, in custody, with attorney Nicole M Masnica.   David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Penalty enhancer, repeater allegation in count 1 stricken.
Defendant entered a plea of guilty to count 1. Court conducted plea colloquy with defendant.
Court strikes the repeater allegation in count 1 and found the defendant guilty of count 1.
Counts 2 and 3 dismissed and read-in.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE of: 

3 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT 97 days IF REVOKED)
1 YEAR, 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2  YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  victim or his residence;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $0.00;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of probation/extended supervision;

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 to be paid as a condition of probation/extended supervision;

CONDITION TIME:  75 DAYS  NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions STAYED (To be used at agent's discretion). 

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

If defendant not released before 3:30pm, then he is to report to the Probation office no later than Monday, 10/26/15 by 9:00 a.m.
